          <p>Not automatically. While wages generally tend to rise over the long term as the cost of living increases, they often lag behind inflation. During periods of rapid inflation, your purchasing power may decline if your employer does not offer raises that match or exceed the inflation rate. Securing inflation-beating wage increases often requires negotiation or switching jobs.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

